Key Match Events: Mohamed Bayo scored a last-gasp winner with just 22 seconds remaining in stoppage time.
Equatorial Guinea was awarded a penalty for a foul by Sekou Sylla on Iban Salvador, but captain Emilio Nsue hit the base of a post with his spot-kick.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was a poor-quality game and looked destined for extra time.
The majority of the stoppage time came from a lengthy VAR check.
